<h2 class="nounderline">Marketing Director</h2>

<p><strong>POSITION:</strong> Marketing Director<br />
  <strong>SUPERVISOR: </strong>Paula F. Goldberg, Executive Director<br />
  <strong>STATUS: </strong>Full-time, Exempt</p>
<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES: </strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>Develop and facilitate a national strategic marketing plan to increase the exposure to and knowledge of PACER&rsquo;s projects and events.</li>
  <li>Coordinate, engage, and work with PACER&rsquo;s Marketing Advisory Board.</li>
  <li>Solicit pro-bono work from marketing and PR firms concerning PACER&rsquo;s branding and media outreach.</li>
  <li>Build PACER&rsquo;s go-to-market strategy to increase PACER&rsquo;s visibility and reach new constituents.</li>
  <li>Utilize digital assets to assist in marketing and communications efforts.</li>
  <li>Ensure all messages are accurate and on brand across all media platforms.</li>
  <li>Work with PACER&rsquo;s communication&rsquo;s staff on forming relationships with respected state and national media.</li>
  <li>Develop email marketing and constituent engagement platforms, including a user generated content strategy.</li>
  <li>Work in partnership with the Executive Director on business development and cause marketing, including the National Bullying Prevention Center.</li>
  <li>Become knowledgeable on Individuals with Disabilities Education ACT (IDEA) and disability related content, as well as bullying prevention related content.</li>
  <li>Other duties as required.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong></p>
<ul type="disc">
  <li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in marketing      or similar field, and 5 years&rsquo; experience working in marketing</li>
  <li>Experience      with building relationships with corporate sponsors, PR firms, and other      high level partners</li>
  <li>Ability      to manage several projects at once while adhering to deadlines</li>
  <li>Strong      organizational skills and attention to detail</li>
  <li>Strong      digital marketing and writing skills</li>
  <li>Experience      in leading programs to scale and outcome-oriented</li>
  <li>Assertiveness&nbsp;in      initiating new projects&nbsp;</li>
  <li>Ability      to think creatively</li>
  <li>Ability      to work independently as well as in team planning</li>
  <li>Knowledge      of and sensitivity to issues experienced by persons with disabilities</li>
</ul>
<p>Parents of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
  Salary to be determined based on experience. Position available immediately.</p>
